claim.claim-text:
A method for braking a materials handling vehicle (10) as claimed in claim 7 further comprising the steps of:
determining an operating speed of said vehicle (10);
starting a timer when said operating speed of said vehicle (10) falls below a first given speed;
upon expiration of said timer determining whether said operating speed exceeds a second given speed; and
fully applying said mechanical brake (44) if said operating speed exceeds said second given speed upon expiration of said timer.

A braking system for a materials handling vehicle (10) as claimed in claim 21 wherein said materials handling vehicle (10) has a drive wheel (50) driven by a traction motor (42) and a mechanical brake (44) associated with said drive wheel (50), said computer (300) being further programmed to:
determine an operating speed of said vehicle (10);
start a timer when said operating speed of said vehicle (10) falls below a first given speed;
upon expiration of said timer determine whether said operating speed exceeds a second given speed; and
fully apply said mechanical brake (44) if said operating speed exceeds said second given speed upon expiration of said timer.

